- Deformity-alignment and contour changes
- Swelling/edema- due to inflammatory process and hematoma formation
- Ecchymosis (bruising)-due to subcutaneous bleeding
- Muscle spasm-involuntary muscle contraction near fracture
- Pain-immediate severe pain due to injury. pain due to muscle spasm later and due to inflammation
$\checkmark$ Bone pain is x-terised as dull \&deep
$\checkmark$ Muscle pain as soreness or aching/muscle cramps
$\checkmark$ \# pain as sharp and piercing relieved by immobilization
$\checkmark$ Sharp pain can also be due to bone infection or pressure on a sensory nerve
$\checkmark$ Pain increasing with activity may indicate joint /muscle sprain,
$\checkmark$ Steadily increasing pain- progression of an infectious process, malignant tumors or neurovascular condition
