\section*{Preoperative}
$\checkmark$ Talk to the client to allay fear and anxiety because of the loss of a limb. Establish open communication and allow the client to express their feelings. If necessary employ the assistance of a social worker or psychologist.
$\checkmark$ Correct the knowledge deficit regarding the amputation and prepare the client for phantom pain/ sensation and also the need for exercise postoperatively.
$\checkmark$ Diabetics are high risk surgical clients and need to be assessed their metabolic status
$\checkmark$ Those with infection given antibiotics and bed rest to promote healing
$\checkmark$ High protein diet and vitamin supplementation
$\checkmark$ If anemic transfusion and hematinics will be necessary
$\checkmark$ Incase of dehydration I.V fluid administration
