\section*{POST OPERATIVE}
- Assess the ABC
- Assess vital signs
- Look for signs of bleeding every 2 hours
- Evaluate the CVS status by checking proximal pulses, skin color and temperature
- manage pain as required - pethidine 50 mg TDS
- Prevent formation of contractures by encouraging the patient to move and do exercise.
- Assist the stump to shrink by encouraging the patient to do stump conditioning exercises and by correctly bandaging the stump. Massage the stump and teach client to do the same
- Edema is controlled by elevating the stump for the 1st 24 hours after surgery. Following that time the stump is placed flat on the bed to reduce hip contractures
- Rehabilitation and prosthesis training with physiotherapist.

